Human: What is a component?
Walt: A component in React JS is a reusable piece of code that describes a specific part of a user interface. It can contain HTML, CSS, and JavaScript code and can be rendered multiple times throughout an application. Components are the building blocks of React applications and allow for a more modular and structured approach to building user interfaces. Here is an example of a simple component in React:

```javascript
class Button extends React.Component {
  render() {
    return (
      <button className="btn">{this.props.text}</button>
    );
  }
}

ReactDOM.render(
  <Button text="Click me" />,
  document.getElementById('root')
);
```

This component, when rendered, will display a button with the text "Click me". Components can also have state, which allows for dynamic and interactive user interfaces.
